The much-awaited 2023 Youth League of the Nationwide League One (NLO) will kick off on Wednesday, July 12 2023. According to a directive from the secretariat, the management of the Nigeria’s third tier league reiterated that participation in the league is restricted to players of age 19 years and below which means only players born from January 2004 above are eligible to participate. “We equally advise all clubs to kindly adhere strictly to this guideline to support the development of football in Nigeria as more screening shall be done at the venues.” The statement reads.